@zloyden @BlazDT Through testing I was able to get the slide-up panel removed with the below rule, without breaking anything with Reddit.com on Safari 26.3.

Do you see any issues with this fix, preventing it from being pushed to AdGuard's filters?

`reddit.com##rpl-modal-card:has([aria-label="Close"]):has(a[data-testid="primary-button"])`
